Hi Akshit, I have a couple of comments on your commit message.

Also, please avoid setting CR+1 on your own changes. If you were trying to indicate it was ready for review, then pushing it to Gerrit is enough. If you wish to push patches to Gerrit that shouldn't yet be reviewed, please use Gerrit's Work-in-Progress feature to mark them as such.
Add description for solution also
Done
Should this be added as a supported fan type?
No this is part of nuvoton's fan type and it is added here - https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/63150

there are multiple sensor services do similar function, it would be nice to use the same function.
maybe base function from this section:
https://github.com/openbmc/dbus-sensors/blob/master/src/HwmonTempMain.cpp#L301
or here:
https://github.com/openbmc/dbus-sensors/blob/master/src/PSUSensorMain.cpp#L371
Changed for other services as well.
Regex is slow, and not really needed for this use case.  The old code that used find() didn't seem to have a problem, so long as the string->value conversion didn't throw?
Fansensor daemon didn't have try catch around stoi() and hence it crashed. I didn't realize regex is slower and would impact significant performance. Changed it to fin()

For new code that's immediately catching the exception, this should really be using std::from_chars which handles under/overflow properly, and doesn't require a c-style cast (which would normally fail clang-tidy.  There's lots of examples of how to do that around.  bmcweb has a bunch if you need one.
Done
